description: This column is about storing the first name of contacts that are visible to the public in the context of managing contacts and identities within the project.

This column is about storing the LinkedIn profile or handle of contacts who are part of the public category.

This column is about identifying the provider of the authentication identity for a user in the system. It likely stores a unique identifier (such as a number or code) that corresponds to the provider of the authentication service used by the user.

description: This column is about storing the user agent information associated with authentication sessions. It may contain details about the web browser, device, or software used by the user during the session.
This column is about categorizing sessions in the authentication module.
This column is about identifying the unique identifier for the authentication user.
This column is about storing the role or privilege level of authentication users in the system. It indicates the specific permissions or access rights that a user has within the application.
This column is about storing the email addresses of users who are authenticated in the system.
This column is about storing the hashed and encrypted password of the users for authentication purposes.
This column is used to store the confirmation token for user authentication and account verification purposes.
This column is used to store the recovery token for authentication users. It likely contains unique tokens that are generated when a user needs to recover their account or reset their password.

This column is used to store the token that is generated when a user requests to change their email address. It is part of the authentication functionality within the project, allowing users to update their email address securely.
This column is about tracking the new email address when a user requests to change their email in the authentication system.
This column is about storing email addresses of public users who have access to the system.
